text: But market rates colapsed in the last two years
New puppie Daisy says volatility is underpriced- I am obliging. Buying more $vxx at $24.62

@realmoney Volatility is Underpriced... Again With the recent rally, complacency has returned. And I am reinitiating a trading long rental in VXX at $24.74. @tomkeene @jimcramer @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney

@realmoney An Inside Day For a change, an inside day. Nevertheless, market breadth has a nice tone (1800 advancers and only 1100 decliners). I listened carefully to the commentary in the financial media today after the labor report and took notes.

To a person the bullish cabal was unconcerned with the employment data (not only was the headline weak but the private sector payroll diffusion index tumbled to a 40 month low at 53.5%) which underscores my thinking that so many simply worship at the altar of price (momentum)

and shape their narrative to fit the news backdrop. Indeed with as much as 80% of the trading derived from the activity of ETFs and machines/algos we are all momentum players now and the market is now one big casino. The all too confident moving monkeys (who believe in the

importance and integrity of the moving averages) then pile on the aforementioned products and strategies that shove prices higher (this week). (Memo to those fin TV commentators - if it was so easy every 10 year old would drop out of elementary school and trade against the moving

averages). I prefer to listen to The Oracle who famously stated, "The market in the short term is a voting machine and in the long run it is a weighing machine." And my scale is currently tipped over to excessive optimism and to elevated stock prices. In the fullness of time.
To my haters, lovers and those that don't give a crap -- enjoy the weekend! @tomkeene @SquawkCNBC @lizclaman

Coming up this morning on @realmoney @jimcramer "Advantage Mr. Market and Mrs. (Serena) Williams" Cramer and the Anti-Cramer (me) square off on the markets (again!) - in a respectful and analytical manner.
